    <meta name="description" content="PREHEAT OVEN TO 475 degrees F (240-250 degrees C). This is what you'll roast it at for the ENTIRE time. Since this employs the use of a VERY hot oven, make sure your oven is..."><meta name="image_src" content="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/kNt70RU1W2TRzxGjyEHmAY4Lp_cGAFKPUBXJWjVEkCSIORSfuyiS9s0WvWzXCqnCJ47QOwIodmD89V_C07GSHWfN2qqyv9pazYukS94xqZc8ytQvAm6d=w600"><link rel="canonical" href="https://www.justapinch.com/recipes/main-course/turkey/2-hour-turkey-really-3.html" /><meta property="og:site" content="Just A Pinch Recipes"><meta property="og:site_name" content="Just A Pinch Recipes" /><meta property="og:title" content="2-Hour Turkey, Really."><meta property="og:type" content="justapinch:recipe"><meta property="og:description" content="The flavor is all that you would expect from a Thanksgiving turkey, but the technique is different! The trick is roasting it on high heat and having the turkey wide open."><meta property="og:url" content="https://www.justapinch.com/recipe/torrey-moseley/2-hour-turkey-really/quick-easy-healthy-turkey"><meta property="og:image" content="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/kNt70RU1W2TRzxGjyEHmAY4Lp_cGAFKPUBXJWjVEkCSIORSfuyiS9s0WvWzXCqnCJ47QOwIodmD89V_C07GSHWfN2qqyv9pazYukS94xqZc8ytQvAm6d=w1200-h630-p-rj-l75"><meta property="og:rating" content="1"><meta property="og:rating_scale" content="5"><meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image"><meta name="twitter:site" content="@justapinchcooks"><meta name="twitter:title" content="2-Hour Turkey, Really."><meta name="twitter:description" content="The flavor is all that you would expect from a Thanksgiving turkey, but the technique is different! The trick is roasting it on high heat and having the turkey wide open."><meta name="twitter:image" content="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/kNt70RU1W2TRzxGjyEHmAY4Lp_cGAFKPUBXJWjVEkCSIORSfuyiS9s0WvWzXCqnCJ47QOwIodmD89V_C07GSHWfN2qqyv9pazYukS94xqZc8ytQvAm6d=s1200-p">
    <script id="justapinch-schema-1" type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"http://schema.org/","@type":"Recipe","name":"2-Hour Turkey","url":"https://www.justapinch.com/recipes/main-course/turkey/2-hour-turkey-really-3.html","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Torrey Moseley","url":"https://www.justapinch.com/me/Torrey","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/pMgFVhpo3-Xh32jpEDiia6jdqAfrCiPFuoGNaep_B-OSfC5GGWWuCOfADRsEaX7S9vW3S6vrB7Xnrr9WnrF2qWZbEW-0-CxwrbZQKV0=s64-p"},"datePublished":"2011-07-17T08:21:17","dateModified":"2025-10-28T12:28:25","publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Just A Pinch Recipes","url":"https://www.justapinch.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.justapinch.com/recipes-build/images/justapinchlogo.png","width":600,"height":60},"brand":"Just A Pinch Recipes","sameAs":["https://www.facebook.com/justapinch","https://www.pinterest.com/justapinchcooks","https://x.com/justapinchcooks","https://www.twitter.com/justapinchcooks","https://www.youtube.com/user/justapinch/videos","https://www.instagram/justapinchcooks","https://flipboard.com/@Justapinchcom","https://www.tiktok.com/@justapinchrecipes","https://www.threads.net/@justapinchcooks","https://apps.apple.com/us/app/pinch-it-recipe-box/id1451513406","https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.justapinch.recipebox"]},"permaId":43075,"image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/kNt70RU1W2TRzxGjyEHmAY4Lp_cGAFKPUBXJWjVEkCSIORSfuyiS9s0WvWzXCqnCJ47QOwIodmD89V_C07GSHWfN2qqyv9pazYukS94xqZc8ytQvAm6d=s600","height":400,"width":600},"description":"The flavor is all that you would expect from a well-cooked Thanksgiving turkey, but the technique is so wonderfully different! The trick is roasting it on high heat and having the turkey wide open. A great time-saver on a holiday when the stove gets a workout. If you find the oven smoking, definitely follow the tip of keeping an inch of water in the pan. The one drawback with this method is you won't have the yummy drippings for gravy as you do from a slow-roasted turkey.","aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":5,"reviewCount":80,"bestRating":5,"worstRating":1},"interactionStatistic":{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/Comment","userInteractionCount":0},"recipeIngredient":["1 - thawed, whole turkey (from 10 - 24 pounds)","2 tablespoon(s) olive oil, extra-virgin","1 to 3 teaspoon(s) coarsely ground salt (Kosher or sea)","- freshly ground pepper"],"recipeInstructions":["PREHEAT OVEN TO 475 degrees F (240-250 degrees C). This is what you'll roast it at for the ENTIRE time. Since this employs the use of a VERY hot oven, make sure your oven is CLEAN before you start, AND put about 1 inch of water in the bottom of the roasting pan to reduce the risk of smoking your family out of the house.\n\nNOTE: Even WITH a pristine oven, I still smoked out my house last Thanksgiving... so a tip to cut down on the smoke issue is to add about an inch of water (or broth) to the roaster pan...and keep replenishing it as needed. By doing this, not only was the smoking problem eliminated, but I had terrific drippings for gravy!\n\nPlace oven rack on LOWEST or SECOND-TO-LOWEST position in oven.  The lowest position may be too hot in some ovens since it's directly above the heating elements.","Remove all giblets, neck, pop-up thermometer (if there is one), and any trussing (like the plastic thing that holds the legs together). Rinse turkey THOROUGHLY, inside and out with cool water, letting all water drain out of neck and body cavities. Pat dry, inside and out, with paper towels.","Place on V or U-shaped wire rack in roasting pan, so that turkey doesn't rest on the bottom of the pan. The first time I made this I didn't have a rack, so I just slapped it in my grandmother's old-fashioned blue-enamel roaster pan and it turned out FINE. \n\nIf you don't have a rack...take a long piece of aluminum foil and wad it up into a long rope, then coil it in the bottom of the pan and rest your turkey on that.\n\nNOTE: I STRONGLY RECOMMEND KEEPING 1-2 INCHES OF WATER IN THE BOTTOM OF YOUR ROASTING PAN DURING COOKING. This will GREATLY reduce smoking (which can be brutal). The first year I made this, I didn't put water in the bottom of the pan...and I smoked out my house. The turkey was fabulous, but the house was SO smoky.","Rub the entire outside of dried-off turkey with olive oil. Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper. I use Kosher salt because it has large, coarse grains.","Pull wing tips AWAY from the body, twist them and tuck them, backward, under the bird... up by its neck.","Using aluminum foil, form caps over the end of each drumstick. If any parts of the turkey extend beyond the pan rim, make a foil \"collar\" underneath to make sure drippings flow back into the pan. Do NOT tie legs together, do NOT add stuffing, do NOT close body cavity. It's probably okay to put a little seasoning in the cavity (herbs, lemon, onion) but don't fill up the cavity.","Pour 2 inches of water into the bottom of the pan.","Bake on the 2nd to lowest rack in the oven.","Halfway through cooking time, turn the roasting pan around 180 degrees to ensure even cooking. Do NOT flip the bird over.","It's done when the internal temp (in the thickest part of BOTH the THIGH and BREAST is 160 degrees. Make certain they are BOTH at temp. Sometimes the thighs take a bit longer. When done, remove from the oven.\n\nApproximate Cooking Timing:\n10-13 lbs. = 50 minutes to 1 1/4 hrs.\n13-16 lbs. = 1 1/4 hrs to 1 hour 50 minutes.\n16-19 lbs. = 1 1/2 hrs to 2 hrs.\n19-22 lbs. = 1 3/4 hrs to 2 1/4 hrs.\n22-24 lbs. = 2 hrs to 2 1/2 hrs.\n25+ lbs. = 2 1/4 to 2 3/4 hrs...or a bit more depending on how humongous it is. Are you sure it's not an ostrich you're roasting? If not, call the Guinness Book of Records.","Cover completely with foil and let rest 30-45 minutes before carving. The internal temp will continue to rise to the recommended 165 degrees. After resting, transfer to a platter for carving. \n\nNOTE: There will likely be a lot of juices in the cavity. Drain them before transferring the bird to a platter. Save the juices to make gravy or moisten dressing."],"nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"778 kcal ","carbohydrateContent":"0 g ","cholesterolContent":"386 mg ","fatContent":"33 g ","fiberContent":"0 g ","proteinContent":"116 g ","saturatedFatContent":"8 g ","sodiumContent":"795 mg ","sugarContent":"0 g ","unsaturatedFatContent":"24 g "},"video":{"@type":"VideoObject","name":"2 Hour Turkey","embedUrl":"https://youtu.be/Thx8qtu4NMo","contentUrl":"https://youtu.be/Thx8qtu4NMo","description":"I ran across this recipe a few years back from my local grocery store. I was very skeptical that one could cook an entire turkey (regardless of size) in about 2 hours and have it edible. Well, not only does this actually work, it produces the BEST roasted turkey I've had to date. No more getting up at 4 a.m. to start the holiday turkey, NO MORE BASTING. It's so incredibly fast and easy. It has become the only way I roast turkeys. Turkey...it's not JUST for holidays, anymore. The biggest turkey I made this way was 22.5 pounds. It took about 2 hours 15 minutes to cook. WOW.","thumbnailUrl":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Thx8qtu4NMo/hqdefault.jpg","uploadDate":"2021-06-15T13:30:00-05:00"},"review":[[{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Barbara Nazworth"},"reviewBody":"I tried this recipe about 8 years ago when my daughter was giving birth on Thanksgiving Day and ended up having to do all the cooking for 2 families.  So I gave it a chance and it went perfectly and saved me sooo much time.  This recipe was literally a lifesaver. This year my sister and I will be using this recipe and I'm excited to use it again.  To anyone out there who is a skeptic, just give it a try, it really is a wonderful recipe and it works."},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kae Hutchens"},"reviewBody":"I used this recipe for the first time back in 2012. It was the first year that I was ever in charge of making a turkey and I was TERRIFIED. I googled easy turkey recipes and this came up, and it has yet to fail me. I used it for this past Thanksgiving which makes 5 years in a row that I've used this method and I'd recommend it to ANYONE tasked with wrangling turkey dinner. Prep is easy, it is delicious whether you brine it beforehand or not (this year was the first year I didn't brine and it was still amazing), and timing is always perfect for me, as I prep my sides while the turkey cooks and then cook them all while it rests afterwards."},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Becky Mears"},"reviewBody":"I suppose since I have used this recipe for the past three years, I should share how incredible it is, how easy, how tasty, how enjoyable it is!  I have never been \"assigned\" to do the turkey before things changed in my family three years ago and there were doubtful family members who almost fainted when I told them I was going to try the two-hour turkey.  It was a great hit and the family always looks forward to it--I would be in trouble if I tried to change now!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Terri Bryant"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Claudia Crassweller"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Margaret Benjamin"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Charlotte Melching"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lisa Lopes"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Tammy T"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Joan Gilbert"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Marilyn Titlebaum"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Judith Erva"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Abby Cooper"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Maria O Padron"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Deanna Williams"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Dixie Dixie"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Candi Hummer"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"jen law"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Amanda Bryant"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Peggy Lawhon"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Bee Anderson"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Carol Lyman"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Seasons Clayton"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jan W"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kirari Sunga"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"REBECCA FLOYD"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Linda Seide"},"reviewBody":"Family Tested & Approved!"},{"@type":"Review","ReviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kitchen Crew"},"reviewBody":"The flavor is all that you would expect from a well-cooked Thanksgiving turkey, but the technique is so wonderfully different! The trick is roasting it on high heat and having the turkey wide open. A great time-saver on a holiday when the stove gets a workout. If you find the oven smoking, definitely follow the tip of keeping an inch of water in the pan. The one drawback with this method is you won't have the yummy drippings for gravy as you do from a slow-roasted turkey."}]],"recipeYield":"12 serving(s)","prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT2H","recipeCuisine":"American","award":"Just A Pinch Blue Ribbon","recipeCategory":"Turkey","keywords":"turkey,2 hour,American,Turkey,Bake","mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":["WebPage"],"@id":"https://www.justapinch.com/recipes/main-course/turkey/2-hour-turkey-really-3.html","breadcrumb":{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"item":{"@id":"https://www.justapinch.com/recipes/main-course","name":"Main Course"}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"item":{"@id":"https://www.justapinch.com/recipes/main-course/turkey","name":"Turkey"}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"item":{"@id":"https://www.justapinch.com/recipes/main-course/turkey/2-hour-turkey-really-3.html","name":"2-Hour Turkey, Really."}}]},"reviewedBy":[{"@type":"Person","name":"The Just A Pinch Test Kitchen","url":"https://www.justapinch.com/kitchen/crew","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/9BHU1N5eTtH1hReBXdt-5MaGnddG-3ezNGqbSNMKa4h047nkSqgbw8x-yhLEQERbF8iPU8rY_ZookJVeltAOXdKO7IiSKipACeyxy70-s64-p"}],"lastReviewed":"2025-10-28T12:28:25"}}</script>
