            <div id="recipe-ingredients">
                <div id="recipe-ingredients" class="text-left mb-3 mb-lg-5">

    <h2 class="mb-3  text-capitalize">Ingredients</h2>

    <ul class="checklist-ul" id="recipe-ingredients-list">
                                <li class="mb-3">
                <strong data-ingrient-quantity class="mr-1">
                    1                                    </strong>
                <span data-ingredient-name>thawed, whole turkey (from 10 - 24 pounds)</span>
            </li>
                                <li class="mb-3">
                <strong data-ingrient-quantity class="mr-1">
                    2                    tablespoons                </strong>
                <span data-ingredient-name>olive oil, extra-virgin</span>
            </li>
                                <li class="mb-3">
                <strong data-ingrient-quantity class="mr-1">
                    1 to 3                    teaspoons                </strong>
                <span data-ingredient-name>coarsely ground salt (Kosher or sea)</span>
            </li>
                                <li class="mb-3">
                <strong data-ingrient-quantity class="mr-1">
                                                        </strong>
                <span data-ingredient-name>freshly ground pepper</span>
            </li>
            </ul>
</div>
                </div>

            <div id="recipe-preparation-container" class="mt-3">

                    <div id="recipe-directions" class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-capitalize">How To Make 2-hour turkey, really.</h2>

        
        <ul id="recipe-preparation" class="list-unstyled">
            
                
                <li class="card bg-transparent border-0 rcp-direction-item mx-auto mb-4">

                                        <div class="rounded bg-dark no-print position-relative animate-all mb-3" data-direction-image style="padding-top:67%;height:0;width:100%;">
                        <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAwACAIAAAP///////yH5BAUAAAEALAAAAAADAAIAAAIChF8AOw=="                              style="opacity:0.01; top:0; left:0; right: 0; bottom:0;"
                             data-aspect-ratio=".67"                              data-lazy-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/t72ri0ZBpBKcKcOO95XsIFECoS1W7nG2WczKkr6El5eFKJVWuDt_dxbsyKctQpJTbJqgZEINrzDAt-FiXSRXDeCCHG2CqbJ0YggRz_TufHFsOeHRfhbs=w750"
                             alt="Clean oven set to preheat to 475 degrees."
                             class="rounded fade-img w-100 h-100 position-absolute no-print " />
                    </div>



                    

                    <div class="font-weight-bold small text-uppercase">Step 1</div>
                    <div class="flex-fill recipe-direction rcp-ugc-block">PREHEAT OVEN TO 475 degrees F (240-250 degrees C). This is what you'll roast it at for the ENTIRE time. Since this employs the use of a VERY hot oven, make sure your oven is CLEAN before you start, AND put about 1 inch of water in the bottom of the roasting pan to reduce the risk of smoking your family out of the house.

NOTE: Even WITH a pristine oven, I still smoked out my house last Thanksgiving... so a tip to cut down on the smoke issue is to add about an inch of water (or broth) to the roaster pan...and keep replenishing it as needed. By doing this, not only was the smoking problem eliminated, but I had terrific drippings for gravy!

Place oven rack on LOWEST or SECOND-TO-LOWEST position in oven.  The lowest position may be too hot in some ovens since it's directly above the heating elements.</div>

                </li>

            
                        <div id="link-box-wrapper" class="ad-unit-wrap rounded no-print">
            <div id="link-box" class="doli-added ad-container ad-loading ad-unit text-center"></div>
        </div>
        
                <li class="card bg-transparent border-0 rcp-direction-item mx-auto mb-4">

                                        <div class="rounded bg-dark no-print position-relative animate-all mb-3" data-direction-image style="padding-top:67%;height:0;width:100%;">
                        <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAwACAIAAAP///////yH5BAUAAAEALAAAAAADAAIAAAIChF8AOw=="                              style="opacity:0.01; top:0; left:0; right: 0; bottom:0;"
                             data-aspect-ratio=".67"                              data-lazy-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/hcHDlZ6nGzFK1d-UaqbtkWHcFGZ-joYYoPEjuTd_dqFaaiWbE-nGHZFQnu-qwJr6_dMGG5A7aeSfduaOwvcS_23WJZ0DQU7sb1FHIYT0ikgPSagL-m2e=w750"
                             alt="Rinsing and prepping the turkey."
                             class="rounded fade-img w-100 h-100 position-absolute no-print " />
                    </div>



                    

                    <div class="font-weight-bold small text-uppercase">Step 2</div>
                    <div class="flex-fill recipe-direction rcp-ugc-block">Remove all giblets, neck, pop-up thermometer (if there is one), and any trussing (like the plastic thing that holds the legs together). Rinse turkey THOROUGHLY, inside and out with cool water, letting all water drain out of neck and body cavities. Pat dry, inside and out, with paper towels.</div>

                </li>

            
                
                <li class="card bg-transparent border-0 rcp-direction-item mx-auto mb-4">

                                        <div class="rounded bg-dark no-print position-relative animate-all mb-3" data-direction-image style="padding-top:67%;height:0;width:100%;">
                        <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAwACAIAAAP///////yH5BAUAAAEALAAAAAADAAIAAAIChF8AOw=="                              style="opacity:0.01; top:0; left:0; right: 0; bottom:0;"
                             data-aspect-ratio=".67"                              data-lazy-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/aABUlJUgkbN55rBCk---sAQ1HGbCQ3ded6Xaa7WkjPCXEUUbf4UHdbmwMO2dG0kah3_QWyWBlpU1lIqdYvY51qoE8i2Im5xNSIHQA-lusCatarrY50Ei=w750"
                             alt="Rack placed in a roasting pan."
                             class="rounded fade-img w-100 h-100 position-absolute no-print " />
                    </div>



                    

                    <div class="font-weight-bold small text-uppercase">Step 3</div>
                    <div class="flex-fill recipe-direction rcp-ugc-block">Place on V or U-shaped wire rack in roasting pan, so that turkey doesn't rest on the bottom of the pan. The first time I made this I didn't have a rack, so I just slapped it in my grandmother's old-fashioned blue-enamel roaster pan and it turned out FINE. 

If you don't have a rack...take a long piece of aluminum foil and wad it up into a long rope, then coil it in the bottom of the pan and rest your turkey on that.

NOTE: I STRONGLY RECOMMEND KEEPING 1-2 INCHES OF WATER IN THE BOTTOM OF YOUR ROASTING PAN DURING COOKING. This will GREATLY reduce smoking (which can be brutal). The first year I made this, I didn't put water in the bottom of the pan...and I smoked out my house. The turkey was fabulous, but the house was SO smoky.</div>

                </li>

            
                
                <li class="card bg-transparent border-0 rcp-direction-item mx-auto mb-4">

                                        <div class="rounded bg-dark no-print position-relative animate-all mb-3" data-direction-image style="padding-top:67%;height:0;width:100%;">
                        <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAwACAIAAAP///////yH5BAUAAAEALAAAAAADAAIAAAIChF8AOw=="                              style="opacity:0.01; top:0; left:0; right: 0; bottom:0;"
                             data-aspect-ratio=".67"                              data-lazy-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/mRBnZKoBr4a8f8lcYgPYjw1p11cD2c8Duj-l4cPEYrBOsbIKpBowP_DRNfTmycwlxMqa3qc55PVGwwQmlvdBw44F9QqAC_sCRrLv2tQw8wcYMJv9qW1O=w750"
                             alt="Turkey rubbed in oil and seasoned."
                             class="rounded fade-img w-100 h-100 position-absolute no-print " />
                    </div>



                    

                    <div class="font-weight-bold small text-uppercase">Step 4</div>
                    <div class="flex-fill recipe-direction rcp-ugc-block">Rub the entire outside of dried-off turkey with olive oil. Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper. I use Kosher salt because it has large, coarse grains.</div>

                </li>

            
                
                <li class="card bg-transparent border-0 rcp-direction-item mx-auto mb-4">

                                        <div class="rounded bg-dark no-print position-relative animate-all mb-3" data-direction-image style="padding-top:67%;height:0;width:100%;">
                        <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAwACAIAAAP///////yH5BAUAAAEALAAAAAADAAIAAAIChF8AOw=="                              style="opacity:0.01; top:0; left:0; right: 0; bottom:0;"
                             data-aspect-ratio=".67"                              data-lazy-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/djIc5El-0EpGNKgh6sIFq3ItnButs6vacBEinluT97NLkQcsOqlc9_SLWW6m5e0ZuBQZJ5D4YfKKS6P91gpWQIXWw6avlP9lCO1tWXpOIeTNbhqz0q9h=w750"
                             alt="Tucking the wings."
                             class="rounded fade-img w-100 h-100 position-absolute no-print " />
                    </div>



                    

                    <div class="font-weight-bold small text-uppercase">Step 5</div>
                    <div class="flex-fill recipe-direction rcp-ugc-block">Pull wing tips AWAY from the body, twist them and tuck them, backward, under the bird... up by its neck.</div>

                </li>

            
                
                <li class="card bg-transparent border-0 rcp-direction-item mx-auto mb-4">

                                        <div class="rounded bg-dark no-print position-relative animate-all mb-3" data-direction-image style="padding-top:67%;height:0;width:100%;">
                        <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAwACAIAAAP///////yH5BAUAAAEALAAAAAADAAIAAAIChF8AOw=="                              style="opacity:0.01; top:0; left:0; right: 0; bottom:0;"
                             data-aspect-ratio=".67"                              data-lazy-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/CInJ0ZTKJq5ZgEzB0J2elT1d3fIx0MB2firCC6ra6-h9jr3VW8RbWHq1G6N_5blmiZ-Bx4DLMiVXHwE7mdOnn58WhG2_es1HWDl04EiTx-qVqZdg1Jw=w750"
                             alt="Covering drumsticks in foil."
                             class="rounded fade-img w-100 h-100 position-absolute no-print " />
                    </div>



                    

                    <div class="font-weight-bold small text-uppercase">Step 6</div>
                    <div class="flex-fill recipe-direction rcp-ugc-block">Using aluminum foil, form caps over the end of each drumstick. If any parts of the turkey extend beyond the pan rim, make a foil "collar" underneath to make sure drippings flow back into the pan. Do NOT tie legs together, do NOT add stuffing, do NOT close body cavity. It's probably okay to put a little seasoning in the cavity (herbs, lemon, onion) but don't fill up the cavity.</div>

                </li>

            
                
                <li class="card bg-transparent border-0 rcp-direction-item mx-auto mb-4">

                                        <div class="rounded bg-dark no-print position-relative animate-all mb-3" data-direction-image style="padding-top:67%;height:0;width:100%;">
                        <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAwACAIAAAP///////yH5BAUAAAEALAAAAAADAAIAAAIChF8AOw=="                              style="opacity:0.01; top:0; left:0; right: 0; bottom:0;"
                             data-aspect-ratio=".67"                              data-lazy-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/lvDZ4CQ8IIuMQbVSka2CUowck2rDU6DpV7ABjXMibgtmHIslSwM3D1DWW6gjUBLkfRqJ6FCuAwFsXJzfZYFZW8CPL8pEHXs0C-viU2aoNQlEcXKmsFev9w=w750"
                             alt="Adding water to the bottom of the roasting pan."
                             class="rounded fade-img w-100 h-100 position-absolute no-print " />
                    </div>



                    

                    <div class="font-weight-bold small text-uppercase">Step 7</div>
                    <div class="flex-fill recipe-direction rcp-ugc-block">Pour 2 inches of water into the bottom of the pan.</div>

                </li>

            
                
                <li class="card bg-transparent border-0 rcp-direction-item mx-auto mb-4">

                                        <div class="rounded bg-dark no-print position-relative animate-all mb-3" data-direction-image style="padding-top:67%;height:0;width:100%;">
                        <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAwACAIAAAP///////yH5BAUAAAEALAAAAAADAAIAAAIChF8AOw=="                              style="opacity:0.01; top:0; left:0; right: 0; bottom:0;"
                             data-aspect-ratio=".67"                              data-lazy-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/nFgLbavtBflJ6q3i2dB6aPMeHrA5Z-nZ3qJI2kn1lrhhPDkvrROVzN3hH4BaD2UqLsSXNh8EUgqivPXFPX7FChvlGZ4iM5uVwje17L0fX7r4g4VQsWU=w750"
                             alt="Turkey in a roasting pan in the oven."
                             class="rounded fade-img w-100 h-100 position-absolute no-print " />
                    </div>



                    

                    <div class="font-weight-bold small text-uppercase">Step 8</div>
                    <div class="flex-fill recipe-direction rcp-ugc-block">Bake on the 2nd to lowest rack in the oven.</div>

                </li>

            
                
                <li class="card bg-transparent border-0 rcp-direction-item mx-auto mb-4">

                                        <div class="rounded bg-dark no-print position-relative animate-all mb-3" data-direction-image style="padding-top:67%;height:0;width:100%;">
                        <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAwACAIAAAP///////yH5BAUAAAEALAAAAAADAAIAAAIChF8AOw=="                              style="opacity:0.01; top:0; left:0; right: 0; bottom:0;"
                             data-aspect-ratio=".67"                              data-lazy-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/GjeueRZTSi1PakmDmF-g4w4HNXEFxdzN1m9gROlTZNL-Mo1JjS7dWIyM9cW0yE8KEoQ2U-3V9ZdtZxQZWQkUnSFn6lB-dYA6TnsxnBuEhzgZygRJjeNG=w750"
                             alt="Rotating the turkey while roasting."
                             class="rounded fade-img w-100 h-100 position-absolute no-print " />
                    </div>



                    

                    <div class="font-weight-bold small text-uppercase">Step 9</div>
                    <div class="flex-fill recipe-direction rcp-ugc-block">Halfway through cooking time, turn the roasting pan around 180 degrees to ensure even cooking. Do NOT flip the bird over.</div>

                </li>

            
                
                <li class="card bg-transparent border-0 rcp-direction-item mx-auto mb-4">

                                        <div class="rounded bg-dark no-print position-relative animate-all mb-3" data-direction-image style="padding-top:67%;height:0;width:100%;">
                        <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAwACAIAAAP///////yH5BAUAAAEALAAAAAADAAIAAAIChF8AOw=="                              style="opacity:0.01; top:0; left:0; right: 0; bottom:0;"
                             data-aspect-ratio=".67"                              data-lazy-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/yRzsXFFYD-zyLGEoj4x2HCcVNYvarG_zR0rBVf-JyH1CIW4plsCoRJs0rYzFQRswZ8dph7_OqQB9jVVDOst8ImKrp2cpJxXY-RLOatlcF_7dVk_EEQ_Rbw=w750"
                             alt="Roasting the turkey until 160 degrees."
                             class="rounded fade-img w-100 h-100 position-absolute no-print " />
                    </div>



                    

                    <div class="font-weight-bold small text-uppercase">Step 10</div>
                    <div class="flex-fill recipe-direction rcp-ugc-block">It's done when the internal temp (in the thickest part of BOTH the THIGH and BREAST is 160 degrees. Make certain they are BOTH at temp. Sometimes the thighs take a bit longer. When done, remove from the oven.

Approximate Cooking Timing:
10-13 lbs. = 50 minutes to 1 1/4 hrs.
13-16 lbs. = 1 1/4 hrs to 1 hour 50 minutes.
16-19 lbs. = 1 1/2 hrs to 2 hrs.
19-22 lbs. = 1 3/4 hrs to 2 1/4 hrs.
22-24 lbs. = 2 hrs to 2 1/2 hrs.
25+ lbs. = 2 1/4 to 2 3/4 hrs...or a bit more depending on how humongous it is. Are you sure it's not an ostrich you're roasting? If not, call the Guinness Book of Records.</div>

                </li>

            
                
                <li class="card bg-transparent border-0 rcp-direction-item mx-auto mb-4">

                                        <div class="rounded bg-dark no-print position-relative animate-all mb-3" data-direction-image style="padding-top:67%;height:0;width:100%;">
                        <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAwACAIAAAP///////yH5BAUAAAEALAAAAAADAAIAAAIChF8AOw=="                              style="opacity:0.01; top:0; left:0; right: 0; bottom:0;"
                             data-aspect-ratio=".67"                              data-lazy-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-cHj5GDrePB0xmnh64B-moaY_a1hspfva-5HqGDE0BS4gMI2SKs5opePR8h4z_TrilLSH5aciLKbbFpayqvAzlDVcT2VKwxNuRg9a6CMf7b35s6pLZV-=w750"
                             alt="Turkey covered in foil and resting."
                             class="rounded fade-img w-100 h-100 position-absolute no-print " />
                    </div>



                    

                    <div class="font-weight-bold small text-uppercase">Step 11</div>
                    <div class="flex-fill recipe-direction rcp-ugc-block">Cover completely with foil and let rest 30-45 minutes before carving. The internal temp will continue to rise to the recommended 165 degrees. After resting, transfer to a platter for carving. 

NOTE: There will likely be a lot of juices in the cavity. Drain them before transferring the bird to a platter. Save the juices to make gravy or moisten dressing.</div>

                </li>

                                        <li class="card bg-transparent border-0 rcp-direction-item mb-3 mx-auto no-print" style="max-width:600px;">
                    <div class="rcp-ugc-block">https://youtu.be/Thx8qtu4NMo</div>
                </li>
                        <li class="print-only pt-4 mx-auto" style="max-width:600px;">
                    <strong>Last Step: Don't forget to share!</strong>
                    Post a picture of your finished recipe here and on your favorite social
                    network. Don't forget to tag Just A Pinch and include #justapinchrecipes!
            </li>
        </ul>

    </div>
    <div class="recipe-wake-mode no-print btn btn-block btn-light mb-3" style="display:none"  role="button"></div>

